I took the advice of others and baked the salmon. I cooked the pieces at 350 for 12 min and then broiled for another 3 min. The pieces were pretty thick so they probably could have used 2 min more under the grill to brown and cook to a med. I also reduced the honey so it wasn't as sweet...taste the sauce as you go to determine the sweetness you prefer. My kids (who hate salmon) said it was really good and gobbled it up!! This was soooo easy, fast, and tasty.

