Rating: 4
This is a very good recipe - not really exceptional but definitely a keeper. I thought the glaze was a bit sweet so I might back off the honey a bit and add a little more vinegar next time, but it definitely enhanced the fish, especially the caraway seeds. I used my mortar and pestle to crush the seeds - next time I'll roast/toast them first to enhance the flavor. Also next time might bake the fish first and finish it under the broiler. Cooking it under the broiler for the whole time seemed to overcook the topping. All that said - I am not a fish fan and I'm trying to eat more of it than I have been lately (used to eat it alot, but somehow lost my taste for it). Several times during the meal both my husband and I remarked on how GOOD it was - so it's a keeper!

