Rating: 4
I've made salmon many different ways, and this is a fantastic recipe. My dinner guests said that it was the best salmon they've ever tasted. I used a 1-1/2 pound flat piece and the amount of glaze was perfect. I suppose there could be too much sauce on a thicker piece with less surface area. Try to buy a piece of even thickness - it will be easier to broil. I used Maille Old Style whole grain Dijon mustard and it was the key ingredient - it really cut the sweetness of the honey. I set my broiler temp to 425 - and it was done in exactly 15 minutes - the top was bubbly, with little brown spots. I put the caraway seeds in a small zipper bag and then ran a rolling pin over it a few times to crush them.

