Rating: 4
This recipe is incredible. The glaze is very flavorful and will surprise you. I had a hard time crushing the caraway seeds (amateur ignorance?) so I just included them whole, but it was fine. I also had to cook the salmon a little longer than it recommended. I had a tail end of the salmon, so the middle part was a little bigger than 1.5". How I remedied this was after 14 mins of cooking, I cut the thinner portion and returned the larger part to the oven at 350 degrees (so that the glaze wouldn't burn from the broiler). I cooked for a few more minutes and it turned out fine. I highly recommend trying this recipe as is.

